Texas legislators have proposed a bill that aims to restrict voting rights, following similar moves in Georgia and Florida. This trend has been criticized as an attack on democracy, with a disproportionate impact on Black and Brown Americans. The author argues that in the 21st century, efforts should be focused on making it easier for eligible voters to cast their ballots. They call on Congress to pass the For the People Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act, and urge all Americans to defend democracy and protect the right to vote and the integrity of elections.